<subSubSection id="E316E34A5D7B232F44150534E2873EBD" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="method">
<paragraph id="9A111DC37AD2B53F6717D955D9E1B2EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Method.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="45C5CACD266C7AE6983F593DB3984F48" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Squash preparations were made on root tips obtained from germinating seeds. Root tips were pre-treated with 0.4% colchicine for 3 hours and then fixed in Carnoy fixative solution for 1 hour. After hydrolysis in HCl 1N at 60 Â°C, the tips were stained in leuco-basic fuchsine for 7-8 minutes.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="25CDC5B3EC1E251948B54A6320643465" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="observations">
<paragraph id="C57DA34AAA1278A79B32BE3BCC7EC01F" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Observations.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9BF13A681658B9B353E9B73F057CFBD1" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species is endemic to southern Toscana, and has been only recently described (
<bibRefCitation id="45B07D14C71CAA7E434AA0AE23CECA90" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1756-1051.2008.00361.x" author="Selvi, F" journalOrPublisher="Nordic Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="125 - 133" refId="B26" refString="Selvi, F, 2009. Armeria saviana sp. nov. (Plumbaginaceae) from Central Italy. Nordic Journal of Botany 27: 125 - 133, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1756-1051.2008.00361.x" title="Armeria saviana sp. nov. (Plumbaginaceae) from Central Italy." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1756-1051.2008.00361.x" volume="27" year="2009">Selvi 2009</bibRefCitation>
). It shows a very narrow distribution range on the surroundings of Monte Labbro (Grosseto). 
<taxonomicName id="201EF984BF7B42BF59886970B37853B6" authorityName="Selvi (Plumbaginaceae" authorityYear="2009" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Armeria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Armeria saviana" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saviana">
<emphasis id="45F892C4BD8A839A99D4D72684E75400" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Armeria saviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="25576E60CCBB28E70CBD8F533566217E" genus="A." lsidName="A. denticulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="denticulata">
<emphasis id="6E5E2D29DC50FA09691BA1BD28AA67F0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. denticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it can be distinguished for a few leaf and inflorescence features. The chromosome count reported here confirms the previous count published by 
<bibRefCitation id="FFA9BCC49247F45FA2DAD62643BF29BB" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1756-1051.2008.00361.x" author="Selvi, F" journalOrPublisher="Nordic Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="125 - 133" refId="B26" refString="Selvi, F, 2009. Armeria saviana sp. nov. (Plumbaginaceae) from Central Italy. Nordic Journal of Botany 27: 125 - 133, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1756-1051.2008.00361.x" title="Armeria saviana sp. nov. (Plumbaginaceae) from Central Italy." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1756-1051.2008.00361.x" volume="27" year="2009">Selvi (2009)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
